They don’t call him Dinky for no reason, for this this little foal has been hailed Britain’s smallest donkey.

The miniature donkey weighs just 30lbs and is three times lighter than the average baby horse.

Dinky is no taller than a Wellington boot and is the smallest foal ever born at the Donkey Sanctuary in Sidmouth, Devon.

