Vet Elena Barrio, who has been at the sanctuary for nine years said: ‘As his mum is a miniature donkey he's the smallest foal we've ever had - about the size of a dog.

‘To give you an idea he's about 90 pounds lighter than the average thoroughbred horse foal.

‘He's such a beauty and so delicate - small but perfectly formed and perfectly healthy. No wonder his mum is so proud of him.’

