The owners of the foal’s mother, Summer, gave her to the charity in June when they could no longer care for her on a farm in Oldham, Manchester.

The Donkey Sanctuary does not allow breeding, but Summer was already pregnant when she was rescued.

Dinky is the 15th foal to be born at the sanctuary this year.

People can visit the site, which is open to visitors, and take part in donkey grooming, nature walks and educational activities.

